  "body": "<!--\r\n  Note: if the issue is about documentation or the website, please file it at:\r\n  https://github.com/reactjs/reactjs.org/issues/new\r\n-->\r\n\r\n**Do you want to request a *feature* or report a *bug*?**\r\n\r\nI want to request a feature.\r\n\r\n**What is the current behavior?**\r\n\r\nNo such an API.\r\n\r\n**What is the expected behavior?**\r\n\r\nI'm writing a HOC which could forward ref to the wrapped component. According to the React specification, 'ref' is not allowed to be given to a stateless function component. Need an API to tells whether a component is SFC.\r\n\r\nOf course, we can add the forwarded ref to a component without check whether it is an SFC, just leave the runtime error, but In typescript language, we can not prevent static analysis warnings. Wish some util API to solve this problem and contribute to the component type narrowing.\r\n\r\nNew APIs suggestion: \r\n1. ReactIs.isStatelessFunctionComponent\r\n2. ReactIs.isClassComponent\r\n\r\n**Which versions of React, and which browser / OS are affected by this issue? Did this work in previous versions of React?**\r\nReact & ReactIs: 16.3.4",
